
Collection
- Collection holds the same type of data or different types of data.

Array
- An array is a collection of the same type of data or different types of data. It has fixed size
  - IntArray : It holds int data
  - BooleanArray: It holds boolean data
  - DoubleArray: It holds double data
  - ByteArray: It holds byte data
  - LongArray: It holds long data
  - ShortArray: It holds short data
  - FloatArray: It holds float data
- function
  - arrayOf<String> : holding string data type
  - arrayOf<Fruit> : holding object or model class data
  - array(1,2,"Raj",20.5) : holding different type of data



Immutable collection
This means you only read the value but you cannot write to it.

- List : listOf -> List is similar to arrayOf but it has more helper methods
- Set : setOf -> Store unique values in group
- map : mapOf -> Store key value paired data

Mutable collection
This means you can read or write data to it.

- Mutable List : ArrayList, arrayListOf, mutableListOf
- Mutable Set : mutableSetOf, hashSetOf
- Mutable Map : HashMap, hashMapOf, mutableMapOf
